This project is a Python-based Caesar Cipher tool that allows you to:
â€¢	Encrypt text using a Caesar shift
â€¢	Decrypt text with a known key
â€¢	Automatically brute-force a Caesar-encrypted text without knowing the key
 How to Use
 1. Open Terminal
 2. Navigation to the project folder:

cd ~/PycharmProjects/caesar-cipher

 Run the script:

python3 caesar_cipher.py

 4. Choose one of the following options:
â€¢	1: Encrypt a message
â€¢	2: Decrypt a message (with known key)
â€¢	3: Auto-decrypt (brute-force all key possibilities)
 Features
â€¢	Caesar encryption (with key)
â€¢	Decryption (with key)
â€¢	Brute-force attack (try all 25 possible Caesar keys)
â€¢	Case-sensitive (preserves upper/lower case letters)
â€¢	Works from the terminal, no external libraries needed
